#lang racket

#|
Problem 15: Lattice Paths
Starting in the top left corner of a 2x2 grid and only being able to move to the right and down
there are exactly 6 routes to the bottom right corner

<The image shows three simple black-and-white geometric icons side by side.
Each icon is made of a square divided into smaller sections,
with a bold outline and a small arrow attached.
The arrows point in different directionsn.>

how many such routes are there through a 20x20 grid?

answer:

ok so this is basically just a arrangement problem.

n! / k! . (n-k)!

|#

; given a posint number, returns its factorial
; number -> number
(define (fact n)
  (cond [(zero? n) 1]
        [else (* n (fact (- n 1)))]
        )
  )
(fact 3) ; 3*2*1 = 6
(fact 2) ; 2*1 = 2

; given a number, generate route possibility in an n x n grid
; number -> number
(define (lattice n)
  (let* ((total-moves (* n 2))
         (k (/ total-moves 2))
         )
    (/ (fact total-moves)
       (* (fact k) (fact (- total-moves k)))
       ) 
    )
  )
(lattice 2) ; should return 6
(lattice 20) ; should return X